## probability_density_function
A probability density function $f$ is defined by the three properties it has
    - $\mathbb{P}(a<f<b) = \int_{a}^{b}f(x)dx$
    - $\forall x$ in the domain, $f(x) \ge 0$
    - $\int_{-\infty}^{\infty} = 1$
